# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Vercel deployment excludes.
#
# THE IMPORTANT ONE: api/match/ holds the reverse-match NIGHTLY PIPELINE
# (buildMatchTokens.js, runReverseMatch.js, runNightly.js) + the pure scorer
# module (reverseMatch.js). These are NOT HTTP endpoints — they run in GitHub
# Actions (.github/workflows/reverse_match.yml) against the repo checkout, and
# in the `node --test` suite. Vercel otherwise turns every api/**/*.js into a
# Serverless Function; on the Hobby plan the cap is 12, and these 4 pushed the
# count to 13 → "No more than 12 Serverless Functions" build failure.
# Nothing in the deployed runtime imports api/match/* (verified), so excluding
# the directory is safe and drops the function count to 9.
api/match/

# Repo assets Vercel never serves or executes — keeps the upload lean.
# NOTE: the GENERATOR is excluded; its OUTPUT (seo/*.html, sitemap.xml, robots.txt)
# is committed and MUST ship — that's the whole point of the static SEO pages.
tests/
docs/
ghost-report-generator/
seo-generator/
scripts/
playwright.config.js
playwright-report/
test-results/
